FT  08 DEC 94 / Deutsche Telekom scam probe
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL LINDEMANN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Deutsche Telekom, which is to be privatised soon, yesterday began internal
investigations following press reports that thousands of its employees were
suspected of working with criminal gangs to syphon off the charges from
overseas telephone calls. Police seized documents from a company in
Dusseldorf which deals with telephones and computers and another company in
the city was reported to have run up a bill of DM2m (Pounds 800m) after
making calls to the Dutch Antilles. Neither the police nor Deutsche Telekom
could confirm press reports that losses of up to DM500m had been run up in
the scam. However, the investigations are a setback for the company which
just two weeks ago announced a consortium of leading international banks to
handle the first stage of its privatisation in 1996.
