</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US insurers CNA Financial Corporation and Continental Corporation say they
have signed a definitive agreement under which CNA will acquire Continental
for Dollars 1.1bn in cash, or Dollars 20 a share, Reuter reports from New
York.
Both boards have approved the transaction, the companies said. The
acquisition may be funded with long-term debt or may include a combination
of long-term debt and equity.
Continental will continue to operate independently until the acquisition is
completed. Mr John Mascotte will continue as chairman and chief executive of
Continental for the interim.
Also, a transition team composed of key people from both organisations will
be formed to ensure a smooth combination.
The acquisition is subject to regulatory approval.
