<TEXT>
Westcoast Energy, an expanding western Canada natural gas producer and owner
of a big Ontario distributor, is stepping into the Australian market with
Broken Hill Proprietary as partner.
The two companies will jointly study the feasibility of building a USDollars
300m 400-mile pipeline to bring gas from Bass Strait to the Melbourne and
Sydney areas. Westcoast would supply pipeline construction and operating
expertise.
BHP controls large gas reserves in the Bass Strait off the south east coast,
and its industrial operations are potential gas customers. The Australian
gas market is developing quickly because of environmental concerns about
coal.
