<HEADLINE>
FT  07 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Drew Scientific
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Drew Scientific, the medical technology company, incurred a pre-tax deficit
of Pounds 515,000 for the six months to September 30, against a loss of
Pounds 811,000 in the comparable period.
Last year's losses - which amounted to Pounds 1.49m for the year - resulted
from problems encountered with the Glycomat testing equipment which led to
the product being temporarily suspended.
Sales for the latest six months amounted to Pounds 431,000 (Pounds 420,000).
</TEXT>
