Newport Holdings, the property investment company, has bought two retail
properties for Pounds 1.63m of which Pounds 1.3m will be paid in cash and
the balance by the issue of shares.
One property, in Gloucester, the principal tenant of which is Grand
Metropolitan Restaurants, produces rent of Pounds 105,000 a year. The other,
in Newquay, has 11 tenancies and produces rent of Pounds 55,000 a year.
</TEXT>
