<HEADLINE>
FT  07 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Tibbett makes Austrian purchase from
Unilever
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tibbett &amp; Britten International, a wholly-owned subsidiary of UK-based
distribution group Tibbett &amp; Britten, is to acquire Eskimo-Iglo
Tiefkuhllogistik (TKL), a distribution and logistics company within
Unilever's Austrian frozen foods division.
The deal will be completed on January 1 1995, when an initial cash payment
of Sch100m (Pounds 5.9m) will be made from the parent group's existing
resources for 70 per cent of the Vienna-based company. A further Sch100m is
payable on the final day of the year.
The remaining 30 per cent of TKL's shares will be acquired by January 1 1997
for a performance-related figure of not more than Sch125m, payable in
instalments between 1997 and 2000.
Mr John Harvey, TBI chairman, said: 'This acquisition is consistent with our
strategy of development within our established business sectors while
translating our experience into new markets by working with existing
multinational clients.'
The acquisition will give Tibbett a long-term contract with Unilever and a
well-developed national network.
The deal will also see 500 employees and about 250 refrigerated vehicles
transfer to TBI.
</TEXT>
