constitute a reprise of 1994, with star turns from the likes of Viktor
Gerashchenko, hapless former governor of the central bank axed after
October's rouble crisis. The mayor of Moscow, Yury Luzhkov, is also promised
an outing. With his attachment to undertaking forays into the city's sewage
system, he must be a parodist's gift.
