FT  07 DEC 94 / Barclays suffers firebomb attacks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Police urged vigilance after six firebombs were posted to London branches of
Barclays Bank. They said that more might still be in the mail.
One worker suffered shock and another was slightly injured but declined
treatment when two devices went off as staff opened the post at branches in
Hampstead High Street and Ladbroke Grove.
